<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What is the primary goal of the Federal Reserve's monetary policy?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To maximize employment only</option>
            <option letter="b">To control inflation only</option>
            <option letter="c">To balance employment, price stability, and economic growth</option>
            <option letter="d">To minimize government debt</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Reserve has a dual mandate to promote maximum employment and price stability, while supporting moderate long-term interest rates. This means balancing multiple objectives: maintaining high employment, controlling inflation, and fostering sustainable economic growth.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
